{
  "texts": [
    "Wang et al. [43] proposed DriveMLM, an LLM-based framework that performs closed-loop autonomous driving in realistic simulators, taking figures (x F), system messages x Sm, and user instructions x Ui as inputs, and generating low-level decisions a D l and explanations a E. Shao et al.",
    "[52] proposed LMDrive, a language-guided, end-to-end, closedloop autonomous driving framework that takes camera-LiDAR sensor data x D CL and driving instructions x I d as inputs, and generates vehicle control signals a Cs.Several studies have focused on integrating LLMs with vision-based autonomous driving frameworks.",
    "Pan et al. [42] proposed VLP (Vision-Language-Planning), which exploits language models to bridge the gap between linguistic understanding and autonomous driving.",
    "VLP takes Bird's Eye View (BEV) features, including labels x L, bounding boxes x B, ego-vehicle trajectory x Tego, and other agents' trajectories x Tagents, and generates enhanced BEV feature representations a F BEV for improved reasoning and planning.",
    "Tian et al. [47] introduced DriveVLM, which leverages Vision-Language Models (VLMs) and Chain-of-Thought (CoT) for hierarchical planning, taking image sequences x Is as input and generating meta-actions a Am, decisions a D, and waypoints a W. Knowledge-driven decision-making is another area of inter-est."
  ]
}